Rating: 3
For what this is-- essentially an adult version of mac and cheese--it was surprisingly good. It is also a very flexible recipe. I used penne, a 14.5 oz. can of diced tomatoes with basil, oregano and garlic, and 1 c. of fat free half and half in place of the cream. The FF 1/2 and 1/2 clumped a little, as it will do if heated too long, but it was not noticeable and definitely helped to cut the calories of this dish. I also followed the advice of another reviewer and used a 1/2 t. each of thyme, oregano and basil. A nice touch. I prepared this dish in a hurry and did not read the directions all the way through so the result was that the dish baked for 30 minutes uncovered. A serendipitous deviation from the recipe, however, since I liked the crispy noodles and so did my boyfriend. A good weeknight dish.

