Rating: 3
Tasty-- a good weeknight meal. My 3 year old who usually only likes plain pasta had seconds of this. I did the following modifications: *1 lb pasta (penne or rigatoni is fine) *2 cups ham *1 1/2 c whole milk instead of cream *about 24 oz chopped tomatoes plus about 1/4 c of the juice *about 3/4 to 1 cup peas *do 1/2 c parmesan and 1/2 c mozz instead of all mozz *1/2 tsp EACH thyme, oregano, basil (instead of all thyme) *1/2 c fresh parsley *sauteed mushrooms would also be good, but adds extra work. To me, the baking time and method seemed as if it would yield a really mushy pasta. I undercooked the pasta by about 3 min. Rinse with cold water to stop cooking. Just bake uncovered in 400 oven until bubbly, about 20-25 min., stirring occasionally.

