This was a HUGE hit with my family. My husband claims that I have never made anything better. I did use 2 14oz cans of chopped tomatoes with garlic and onion. Instead of baking it (I was short on time), while I cooked the pasta to not quite al dente, I put everything else in a large skillet. Then I drained and added the pasta after rinsing with cool water. Brought the whole thing to a simmer, covered, simmered 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Then I uncovered and added 1 tbsp cornstarch mixed into 1/4 milk to thicken the sauce. I also substituted Land-o-Lakes fat-free half and half for the cream. Total cooking and prep time was about 25 minutes.

